P = Perseverance of the Saints  Chapter 11 – Regeneration: The New Birth From Above

Summary:

As the story progresses, the theological focus shifts to regeneration — the new birth.
This is not moral reform, emotional stirring, or religious awakening.
It is the sovereign act of God by which a dead heart becomes alive.

Men often believe they can "turn over a new leaf."
But Scripture teaches we need a new life, not a new leaf.

Jonathan Edwards wrote:

"The new birth is a change wrought by God, not an act performed by man."

Regeneration is the fountainhead of faith, repentance, love, and obedience.
It is God creating what was not there.
It is the Spirit doing what flesh cannot.

Key Scriptures:
	•	John 3:3–8 — "Unless one is born again he cannot see the kingdom of God."
	•	Titus 3:4–5 — "He saved us… by the washing of regeneration and renewal of the Holy Spirit."
	•	Ezekiel 36:26 — "I will give you a new heart… and a new spirit I will put within you."
	•	1 Peter 1:3 — "He has caused us to be born again."

⸻

Reflection Questions
	1.	What parts of Jesus' conversation with Nicodemus stand out to you?
	2.	Why do men resist the idea that the new birth is something God must do?
	3.	How does regeneration change the way you think about evangelism?
	4.	What evidence of new birth have you seen in your own life?
	5.	If God is the One who causes new birth, how should that affect your confidence in prayer?

⸻

Group Discussion
	•	Why isn't "trying harder" the same as being born again?
	•	How can we as Christian men cultivate environments (homes, workplaces, friendships) where the Spirit's regenerating work is welcomed and prayed for?
	•	John Bunyan said:
"A man can no more change his own heart than he can create a world."
How does this truth shape your view of Christian growth?
	•	Discuss ways to help unbelieving men see the difference between religion and regeneration.

⸻

Prayer Focus

"Lord, thank You for giving me a new heart and new desires. Continue renewing me by Your Spirit. Make me a man who lives out the power of the new birth in everything I do."

